data.title: Visits by Foreign Leaders
data.text: Prime Minister Seewoosagur Ramgoolam Informal visit. Afterwards visited Cape Kennedy. Departed U.S. May 10. May 8–9, 1968 Prime Minister Seewoosagur Ramgoolam Met with President Nixon in New York City while attending a U.N. General Assembly session. September 18, 1969 Prime Minister Seewoosagur Ramgoolam Attended White House dinner on 25th Anniversary of the U.N. October 24, 1970 Prime Minister Seewoosagur Ramgoolam Private visit while attending U.N. General Assembly session. September 30, 1975 Prime Minister Seewoosagur Ramgoolam Private visit. Met with President Reagan October 16. October 12–16, 1981 Prime Minister Aneerood Jugnauth Official working visit. Private visit to New York afterward. June 4–6, 1991 Prime Minister Anerood Jugnauth Working visit. Also attended United States-Africa Business Summit. June 23–27, 2003
